HEADWORD: Semimetal
<hw>Sem"i*met`al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An element possessing metallic properties in an inferior degree and
not malleable, as arsenic, antimony, bismuth, molybdenum, uranium,
etc.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semimetallic</ent>⟦br⟧
